<TITLE> Ombudsman by Jan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 1 (bdnews24.com)--The government will appoint ombudsman by next January to establish rule of law, the law minister has said. Shafique Ahmed spoke to reporters after a meeting with the country director of Asian Development Bank at his secretariat on Tuesday. He said in October that nominations were being finalised to appoint an ombudsman in line with the constitution. A scrutiny committee, headed by the speaker, had been asked to finalise the nominations. The government will make the appointment after getting the committee's proposal, Shafique has added. On the activities of the ombudsman, the minister said if any person is harassed or harmed by any government actions they can place complaints to the ombudsman. The ombudsman will recommend necessary steps after investigation of complaints. bdnews24.c
